# Database Rules

## Query Patterns
- All DB queries go in `src/lib/db/queries/` — not inline in components
- Group queries by feature: `users.ts`, `posts.ts`
- Always handle `null` returns — never assume data exists

## Drizzle Pattern
```typescript
// ✅ Correct query structure
export async function getUserById(id: string) {
  try {
    const result = await db
      .select()
      .from(users)
      .where(eq(users.id, id))
      .limit(1)
    return result ?? null
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('[getUserById]', error)
    return null
  }
}
```

## Migrations
- Never edit migration files manually after applying
- Always run `drizzle-kit generate` after schema changes
- Test migrations on dev DB before staging
